Security companies and individuals have been in the midst of the action and manning control rooms since the start of the Lowveld’s fuel hike protests on July 6. The spokesperson for the Lowveld Security Joint Operation Command (JOC), Callum mac Pherson, expressed his utmost gratitude from the JOC’s side to everyone who was involved in this initiative. Whether it be by offering up their time, sleep, and sometimes even safety, to keep the residents of Mbombela and surrounds updated on the situation for the last two days. ALSO READ: 37 arrested following protest in the Lowveld The following companies and organisations added their efforts to the initiative:
• Hi-Tech Nelspruit
• Fidelity SIU
• ACS Security
• Divergent Ops
• Taysec Security
• Lowveld Tracking
• Naspoti Security Solutions
• Securicon Nelspruit
• Bossies Community Justice
• Nelspruit Concerned Citizens
• AfriForum Nelspruit
• SRRS
• Urban Africa
• i-Secure. Mac Pherson also thanked Lowvelder and Radio Laeveld for being the JOC’s official communication channels with the public. “And, of course, so many members of the public who provided updates from their side, there are more than we could possibly name and thank.” He apologised if anyone was omitted in the JOC’s thanks, but said any and all who were involved should know that their assistance was greatly appreciated.  